image = cv2.imread(image_path, cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
    if image is None:
        raise FileNotFoundError(f'No image found at {image_path}')
    (rows, columns) = image.shape[:2]

    # create a black histogram of size (256, 3) with a white background
    # (B, G, R, A)
    histogram = np.zeros((256, 3), dtype=np.uint8)
    # loop over the image
    for i in range(rows):
        for j in range(columns):
            # increment the appropriate bin in the histogram
            histogram[image[i, j]][0] += 1

    # plot the histogram
    plt.title('Grayscale Histogram')
    plt.axis([0, 256, 0, 256])
    plt.bar(range(256), histogram[0], width=1, align='edge')
